included.description:
As a team of five, we took the CHI design competition's challenge: "engage communities." We strived to generate a design solution to tackle the world's trash crisis by building a more environmentally conscious community, as well as motivating people to forgo single-use paper/plastic cups and use their own reusable mugs instead in their daily lives.

Using theories of social influence and behavior change, the BYOM interactive system increases participation in eco-friendly behaviors.
- A sleek embedded silicone sleeve that fits onto most travel mugs and integrates with a mobile application to strategically remind users to bring their own mugs
- A mobile app that allows users to view their achievements and environmental impact metrics, along with those of their social networks -- empowering individuals to engage one another and form eco-friendly communities.
included.title: CHI 2018 Design Competition - BYOM (Bring Your Own Mug)

included.description:
Students, especially international students, might occasionally need certain home appliances. However, making purchases of those items is not a feasible solution for those students. Meanwhile, there might be students who own more home items and are not necessarily using them on a frequent basis. 

âGoods Net is designed to connect these two different groups of people. People who have spare home items can list and rent out their items in the app to make extra income, which serves as a primary incentive for those users. And those who are in need of those items can benefit from the app because it offers them an affordable way to get the items when they need them.
included.title: E-commerce Mobile App: Goods Net
